    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing create_ue_eth_if function for SDAP Ethernet interface creation\n\n### Summary\nThe SDAP layer was missing the `create_ue_eth_if` function that users expected to exist for creating UE Ethernet interfaces. When calling this function, the behavior was undefined since it didn't exist.\n\nThis fix implements the missing `create_ue_eth_if` function that properly creates TUN interfaces for UE Ethernet connectivity. The function validates inputs, checks for existing SDAP entities, and creates TUN interfaces with proper error handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/SDAP/nr_sdap/nr_sdap.h`: Added function declaration for `create_ue_eth_if`\n- `openair2/SDAP/nr_sdap/nr_sdap.c`: Implemented the `create_ue_eth_if` function with proper TUN interface creation\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, attempting to call `create_ue_eth_if()` would result in a linker error or undefined behavior since the function didn't exist. After this fix, the function properly creates TUN interfaces and returns 0 on success or -1 on failure.\n\nUsers can now call:\n```c\nint result = create_ue_eth_if(ue_id, pdusession_id, \"oaitun_ue1\");\n```\n\nThe function will create a TUN interface named \"oaitun_ue1\" associated with the specified UE and PDU session, returning 0 on success or -1 if the SDAP entity doesn't exist or interface creation fails.\n"
}